Britam Insurance (Uganda) has unveiled its new offices in Nakasero suburb in Kampala.
 The offices, which were acquired from AIG, will host both Britam Insurance Company (Uganda) Ltd - the insurance arm of Britam Holdings Limited - and Britam Asset Managers Company (Uganda) Ltd.  
 ALSO READ:

NHIF launches new medical scheme for police and prison officers

 Speaking during the unveiling of the offices at a Kampala hotel, Mr Allan Mafabi, the CEO, Britam Insurance - Uganda, said: “We are excited about our new spacious offices. This gives us an opportunity to serve our customers better.”





